.TH SMARTMKTAG 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-utils" "SmartMet Build Tools"
.SH NAME
smartmktag \- tag the commit that introduced the current spec version
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smartmktag
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B smartmktag
finds the unique
.BI smartmet- *.spec
file in the current directory, reads its
.B Version:
and
.B Release:
fields, and walks back through the file's git history to identify the
oldest commit that already declares this exact
.IB version - release
pair (that is, the commit at which the current version was first
introduced). If no git tag of that name exists yet, the script
creates one pointing at that commit; otherwise it reports that the
tag is already present and exits without modifying anything.
.PP
The intended use is:
.BR smartmkrelease (1)
bumps the version, commits the change and creates the tag in one
step. If a release commit was made or pulled without its
corresponding tag (for example by a co\(hymaintainer who edited the
spec by hand),
.B smartmktag
recovers by tagging the right historical commit retroactively.
.PP
Exactly one
.B smartmet-*.spec
file must be present in the current directory; the script aborts
otherwise.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
cd ~/hub/macgyver
.br
smartmktag
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR smartmkrelease (1),
.BR smartbuild (1),
.BR smartbuildrev (1),
.BR git (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
